The West German economy is expected tocontinue to grow at low levels despite a marked slowing ofexpansive forces in early 1987, the German Industry Association(BDI) said.    A BDI statement warned, however, that a sense of proportionin 1987 wage settlements was necessary to ensure that growthwas preserved.    Union representatives and employers in the key engineeringindustry are currently negotiating on 1987's and union claimsfor a shorter working week. Last week public sector employeesreceived a 3.4 pct wage rise retroactive from January 1. REUTER&#3;